AN ACT relating to governmental financial administration;
establishing certain conditions of the acceptance of an
appropriation; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes various provisions relating to state financing and the
2 process of appropriation. (NRS 353.150-353.246) This bill requires an entity, as a
3 condition of the acceptance of any appropriation of public money, to agree to
4 comply with certain civil rights or employment laws that are applicable to the
5 entity.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 353 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. As a condition of the acceptance of any appropriation of
4 public money, an entity must agree to comply with any civil rights
5 or employment laws applicable to the entity, including, without
6 limitation, such laws that contain protections against retaliation
7 for employees who seek to enforce, administer or otherwise
8 promote compliance with the law.
9 2. The acceptance of public money by an entity is deemed
10 the agreement by the entity to the conditions prescribed by
11 subsection 1.
