1 3. As used in this section, “civil rights or employment laws”
2 means any state or federal law which prohibits discrimination
3 because of race, creed, color, national origin, sex, sexual
4 orientation, gender identity or expression, age or disability. The
5 term includes, without limitation:
6 (a) Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, 42 U.S.C. §§
7 2000e et seq.;
8 (b) The Age Discrimination in Employment Act of 1967, 29
9 U.S.C. §§ 621-634;
10 (c) The Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, 42 U.S.C. §§
11 12101 et seq.; and
12 (d) NRS 613.310 to 613.4383, inclusive.
